<section class="panel mb-6 p-6 md:p-8">
  <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100 md:text-2xl">Edge Security and Infrastructure</h2>
  <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-300">
    The dashboard runtime applies explicit cache and security headers at origin while Cloudflare edge policies absorb volatile read load. API paths use short max-age windows and stale-while-revalidate controls, while no-store paths remain uncached.
  </p>

  <div class="mt-5 grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-3">
    <article class="rounded-lg border border-slate-700 bg-slate-900/65 p-4">
      <p class="section-title">Origin Contract</p>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-300">Cache-Control, CDN-Cache-Control, and Cloudflare-CDN-Cache-Control headers are synchronized for deterministic behavior.</p>
    </article>
    <article class="rounded-lg border border-slate-700 bg-slate-900/65 p-4">
      <p class="section-title">Transport and Limits</p>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-300">Security middleware enforces CSP, HSTS-on-HTTPS, and request-rate controls for API traffic before response fanout.</p>
    </article>
    <article class="rounded-lg border border-slate-700 bg-slate-900/65 p-4">
      <p class="section-title">Live Stream Path</p>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-300">WebSocket `/ws` remains a direct realtime channel while REST fallback `/api/status/countdown` supports low-frequency polling clients.</p>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>